Sharp Glacier (6720S 6627W / 67.333S 66.45W / -67.333; -66.45Coordinates: 6720S 6627W / 67.333S 66.45W / -67.333; -66.45) is a glacier flowing north to the head of Lallemand Fjord, close east of the Boyle Mountains, in Graham Land. Mapped by Falkland Islands Dependencies Survey (FIDS) from surveys and air photos, 1948-59. Named by United Kingdom Antarctic Place-Names Committee (UK-APC) for Robert P. Sharp, American geologist who has undertaken numerous studies on glaciers and their flow. This article incorporatespublic domain material from the United States Geological Survey document "Sharp Glacier" (content from the Geographic Names Information System).
